The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Ministry to probe Nabis inclusion

OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

New Delhi: The arrest of an Indian masseur during the Commonwealth Games on charges of sexually assaulting a local girl in Melbourne, has also hit the top brass of Sports Authority of India officials hard. 

According to SAI sources, the Union sports minister, Mani Shankar Aiyar, called up senior SAI officials in Melbourne and wanted to know who included Diwan Asgar Nabis name in the last moment. 

Speaking to The Telegraph on Thursday, a SAI official said: The sports ministry as well as the ministry of external affairs are upset. The sports ministry is enquiring whether Nabis name was included at the last moment at the behest of a top SAI official. 




